# Orchestrator & task board

PipeWatch work is tracked **task-by-task** in **Linear** (team **PipeWatch**, `PW-*`). The MVP phased roadmap is **complete** ‚Äî normal work is **bugs, fixes, and iteration slices**, not epic-queue sweeps.

## Use the orchestrator skill when

- The user asks to "orchestrate", "delegate", or implement a Linear issue (`PW-N`) with verifier gate
- Multi-step work spans several linked tasks (optional epic ‚Äî operator must name the target)

In that case, follow `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/SKILL.md`. Do not improvise.

## Use Linear issues directly when

- You're implementing a single bug or task and the user pointed at `PW-N`
- Scope is small enough that orchestrator overhead is unnecessary

Load the issue via MCP `get_issue`; read acceptance criteria from the description and PRD `¬ß` refs cited there.

## Task lifecycle

| Linear status | Meaning |
|---|---|
| Backlog | Unrefined / deferred |
| Ready | Fully specified ‚Äî orchestrator picks from here |
| In Progress | Execution agent working |
| In Review | Execution done ‚Äî awaiting verifier |
| Done | Verifier PASS ‚Äî commit on `staging`; linked GitHub issue closes on merge to `main` |

**Blocking dependencies:** A task blocked by `PW-N` is **unblocked** when `PW-N`'s Linear status is **Done** or **Closed**.

## Linear board status (when orchestrating)

Team **PipeWatch** on Linear. Operator references **`PW-N`**; commits use **`[#N]`** / **`fixes #N`** (GitHub number from Linear sync).

- **Any orchestrator target** (single leaf or epic) ‚Üí present batch plan with **`PW-N`**, then start immediately unless user said `plan only` / `wait`
- **Execution prompts** ‚Üí paste **STATUS FIRST** block as **first lines** ‚Äî see `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/prompt-templates.md`
- **Execution agents** ‚Üí first MCP call sets **In Progress** (leaf + parent); **In Review** before verifier; output must include `BOARD STATUS: ‚Ä¶`
- **Verification agents** ‚Üí set **Done** after all layers PASS (launch **not** `readonly`); FAIL ‚Üí **Ready** + synced-thread comment
- **Orchestrator** ‚Üí after every verifier PASS, confirm Linear status **Done** and commit-linkage audit (`fixes #N` on `staging`)
- **Forbidden:** condensed `LINEAR SYNC` one-liners ‚Äî use full blocks from `prompt-templates.md`
- Execution prompts must **not** set Done ‚Äî see `.cursor/skills/orchestrator/linear-board.md`

## Universal acceptance criteria (every task)

Even when not listed in an issue, the verifier applies:

- File / directory naming (`04-naming.mdc`)
- Conventional commits with `[#N]` ‚Äî GitHub `#N` resolved from Linear (`07-issue-commit-linking.mdc`)
- TypeScript strict, no `any`, no `console.log` (when TypeScript is in scope)
- Security defaults ‚Äî JWT/refresh/API-key rules, webhook HMAC, workspace scoping (`03-security-baseline.mdc`)
- Edition flags via `packages/config/edition.ts` ‚Äî no scattered edition checks (`00-project.mdc`)
- Vendor-neutral schema names in DB/API (`04-naming.mdc`)
- Drizzle schema + migration workflow (`15-db-migrations-schema.mdc`)
- i18n catalog + no hardcoded UI copy for frontend tasks (`16-i18n.mdc`) ‚Äî `pnpm i18n:validate` and `pnpm i18n:check:hardcoded` when `apps/web` or `packages/ui` TSX/locale JSON changes

## Explicit non-goals (MVP out of scope ‚Äî PRD ¬ß2)

If a request targets any item below, **flag it** and ask whether to defer:

- Webhook Gateway / relay for private CE instances
- Alerts & notification channels (Slack, email)
- Re-running workflows from PipeWatch
- SSO
- Raw log storage / ingestion
- GitHub Enterprise Server
- Additional CI platforms (GitLab, CircleCI, etc.)
- AI-powered failure resolution
